review_blob: For the price, a surprisingly rich brew typical of most Huber products.  REminiscent of the first Augsburger I had in 1977.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: An American "Oktoberfest" that actually vaguely tastes German.  Not quite Spaten but a lot cheaper.  Keep it coming, Jake L.!

One of the few drinkable beers from Gluek in Cold Spring, MN!  Previously, its main appeal was an acceptibly decent taste and a low price of 8.99 a case.  Now the Gluek crew have decided to market this stuff as a premium beer at 7.99 a 12.  Ive gone back to Milwaukees Best.

Until Gluek Light, I have never met a beer that completely undrinkable.  Then I met Gluek Light.  Bitter, fizzy water.  Few Gluek products are palatable, few from the Cold Spring Company before it were any good.  Is it the water?
A puzzling beer that at first tasted like a Huber product but then devolved by beer 6 into a standard City cheap corn brew.  By number 12 it tasted like a Gluek beer which is no compliment at all.
